<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 1:03AM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Calhoun, southern
Barry, Kalamazoo and southwestern Eaton Counties through 200 AM
EDT...
At 102 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Nashville to 7 miles northwest of
Kalamazoo. Movement was southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Albion...
Marshall...            Battle Creek...        Galesburg...
Homer...               Nashville...           Union City...
Bellevue...            Climax...              Richland...
Burlington...          Westwood...            Brownlee Park...
Comstock Northwest...  Level Park-Oak Park... Gull Lake...
Alamo...               Fulton...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM EDT for
south central and southwestern Michigan.</instruction>
